      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWIFT CODE (9) has tackled stronger races at Menangle in both starts off a spell, the first of those in a NSW Oaks heat before finishing 3 metres away from the winner in fourth last week. Raced three without cover there but stuck on so the effort had merit. Draws for a trail and and looks nicely placed. NOTHING FINER (10) produced a better effort when second up last time out, coming from this barrier to miss by a nose at Newcastle. Won the only time she attempted this circuit and distance and should be hitting her peak now as should ENJABONARLO (11) who draws on the back row but has been good in both appearances here since a spell including a placing from a similar barrier to this. SMOOTH BUCKAROO (5) is up in grade but should be respected after coming from wider and scoring last week by 11 metres at this circuit and distance.",
